  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the Requirements**\n\nOkay, I\'m defining the requirements for this \"Premium Restaurant Website Template\" for NorthByte. The \"NorthByte Master Prompt\" is full of instructions and technologies: Next.js 15, GSAP, React Three Fiber, React Hook Form. I\'m focusing on distilling the core needs for restaurant owners from this technical overload to ensure a usable, beautiful product.\n\n\n**Clarifying the Tech Stack**\n\nI\'ve realized a critical detail: we\'re working within a Vite + React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS environment, not Next.js 15, as the initial prompt seemed to suggest. This necessitates a shift in focus. The container\'s configuration and port restrictions (only port 3000 is accessible) further solidify this understanding. I am now double-checking dependencies, starting with `package.json`, to clarify the available packages.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Skill Relevance**\n\nI\'m now prioritizing the most relevant skills for the project. The user\'s focus is on a customizable restaurant website template, so I\'m omitting database integrations, Firebase, OAuth, and maps APIs. I\'m leaning toward a gorgeous, client-side single-page application with premium responsive layouts, animations, and customizable data. The core will be a single config file, such as `restaurant.config.ts`, and multiple views or tabs with smooth section navigation. I\'m focusing on `shadcn-ui`, `workspace-integration`, and perhaps `gemini-api` for content generation if needed. I\'ll perform a skill check first.\n\n\n"
