  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Config Expectations**\n\nI\'m now focusing on defining the configuration expectations for this Premium Restaurant Website Template. The primary goal is ensuring everything is customizable from a single `restaurant.config.ts` file. I\'m investigating how comprehensive this single point of control should be. The idea is to build a highly configurable and easily maintainable template.\n\n\n**Structuring the Configuration**\n\nI\'ve got the essential config items down \342\200\223 restaurant name, logo, colors, and the works. I\'m focusing now on the `/src/config/restaurant.config.ts` structure. I\'m aiming for stunning initial visuals, so I\'m sourcing high-quality food photography URLs from Unsplash to ensure the template\'s instant luxury appeal. Next, I\'m thinking about the website features, specifically a premium loading screen.\n\n\n**Designing UI Elements**\n\nI\'m now deep-diving into the UI, starting with a clean scroll indicator and progress bar at the top. The sticky glass navbar is coming together with the logo, refined links, and that glowing \"Book Table\" button. The interactive hero is next with huge typography, gradient overlays, and those slide-under highlight buttons. I\'m focusing on crafting an intuitive and luxurious user experience.\n\n\n**Adding Menu Interactivity**\n\nMy next focus is on the menu, aiming for intuitive navigation. I\'m adding interactive search, category switching (Veg, Non-Veg, etc.), pricing display, and toggle filters. I\'m imagining a refined visual experience.\n\n\n**Adding Final Touches**\n\nI\'m now integrating social grids, copyright credits, and a dynamic newsletter form complete with interactive success states. I\'m also adding sticky quick actions like a WhatsApp float button, quick reservation trigger, and a back-to-top indicator. Furthermore, I\'ve got a live theme customizer in the works as a bonus for restaurant owners, offering an \"Agency Rebranding Playground\" to demo theme swapping and font changes. I\'m exploring Google Fonts now.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/types.ts` to define the TypeScript types and interfaces for our premium, config-driven restaurant template. This ensures type safety and makes it clean to swap configuration data or plug in a CMS later. Let\'s write the types."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 8
      nanos: 683787481
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
