  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Verifying Requirements Completion**\n\nI\'m pleased to report that the initial checks, `lint_applet` and `compile_applet`, have passed without issue. My current focus is on understanding the user\'s intent more fully. I\'m carefully reviewing the provided prompt for specific file requests and configurations to make sure the user\'s requirements are completely addressed before proceeding.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have successfully built the **Premium Config-Driven Restaurant Website Template** for NorthByte using a modern, performant, and clean tech stack (**React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS v4 + Motion**). \n\nThe template is fully production-ready, highly responsive, and meticulously structured so that changing a single configuration file (`/src/config/restaurant.config.ts`) instantly rebrands the entire website\342\200\224colors, typography, menu lists, background visuals, chef biography, and reservation coordinates.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Design Concept (NorthByte Standards)\n*   **Fonts & Aesthetics**: Features **Cormorant Garamond** (for luxury, editorial serif headings) paired with **Plus Jakarta Sans / Space Grotesk** (for minimalist, high-contrast, geometric layout details) and **JetBrains Mono** (for micro-labels, dates, and currency displays).\n*   **Dark-Mode Immersive Canvas**: Centered around an off-black (#030712) obsidian foundation with glassmorphism panels, glowing golden accent radial lights, and full-bleed culinary visuals.\n*   **Asymmetric Layout Rhythm**: Variations in padding, asymmetric masonry blocks, and margins prevent the website from looking like a basic template, raising the perceived value to easily justify a \342\202\27120k\342\200\223\342\202\27140k customization price point.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\233\240\357\270\217 Config-Driven Architecture\nEverything is driven from a single TypeScript file: `/src/config/restaurant.config.ts`.\nTo showcase this direct customization, I implemented an **Agency Rebranding Playground** in the applet:\n*   **Hot-Swappable Presets**: A floating selector panel lets potential restaurant buyers switch instantly between three custom pre-loaded restaurant concepts:\n    1.  **L\'\303\211toile Fine Dining**: Elegant Champagne Gold & Obsidian theme (French gastronomy).\n    2.  **Sakura Kyoto**: Zen Crimson Red & Charcoal Black theme (Japanese Fusion).\n    3.  **Veloce Trattoria**: Warm Emerald Olive Green & Mediterranean Slate theme (Tuscan Italian).\n*   **Live Title Rebranding**: Users can type custom text into a live input field in the corner of their screen and watch the logo branding, titles, and labels update dynamically across every section.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\223\246 Implemented Functional Modules\n1.  **Premium Loading Screen (`Preloader.tsx`)**: An elegant countdown progression with letter-staggering entrance reveals and fluid wipe transitions.\n2.  **Sticky Glass Header (`Navbar.tsx`)**: Responsive, blur-backed navigation bar with smooth-scroll coordinates, desktop active link tracking, and mobile drawer toggles.\n3.  **Cinematic Hero Screen (`Hero.tsx`)**: Full-screen layout with an automatic, slow Ken Burns zoom-fade visual carousel, subtle mouse-coordinate parallax tiling, and dual action CTAs.\n4.  **Brand Narrative & Stats (`About.tsx`)**: Two-column layout presenting the chef\342\200\231s statement, philosophy, and interactive achievements (e.g. Michelin Star indicators, rare wine cellars).\n5.  **Philosophy Pillars (`WhyChoose.tsx`)**: High-contrast, glassmorphic cards decorated with subtle glows and responsive vector icons.\n6.  **Signatures Spotlight (`SignatureDishes.tsx`)**: Interactive showcases for signature items with hovering zoom overlays, price cards, and direct order actions.\n7.  **Ledger Menu Engine (`MenuSection.tsx`)**: Full-text searching, category tab navigation (Starters, Mains, Desserts, Drinks), and diet filtering (Vegetarian vs Non-Veg). \n    *   *UX Highlight*: Selecting a dish on the menu dynamically populates the \"Concierge Requests\" text field in the booking form and scrolls the user down to the booking desk.\n8.  **Immersive Visual Gallery (`GallerySection.tsx`)**: Asymmetric masonry layout with category filtration and a **built-in Lightbox Carousel** supporting keyboard arrows (`\342\206\220`/`\342\206\222`/`ESC`) and click-based cycling.\n9.  **Chef\'s Career Timeline (`ChefStory.tsx`)**: Biographical profile containing career milestones and a simulated digital cursive signature.\n10. **Patron Testimonials (`Testimonials.tsx`)**: Automated, sliding critic review cards with star grids, customer avatars, and manual bullet triggers.\n11. **Reservation Terminal (`ReservationForm.tsx`)**: Validation form (Full Name, Date, Guest Size counters, Seating Zones, and Diet pills) that yields a **Golden Digital Boarding Ticket Pass** upon submission, complete with barcode illustrations, booking references, and custom print controls.\n12. **Correspondence Hub (`ContactSection.tsx`)**: Operational timetables, WhatsApp floats, email triggers, and a styled map block.\n13. **Sticky Actions (`StickyActions.tsx`)**: Pulsing WhatsApp shortcut button and dynamic Back-to-Top scrolling triggers.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\222\276 Exporting the Template\nSince AI Studio manages the containerized workspace, you can immediately download the complete, clean ZIP archive of this project:\n1.  Open the **Settings Menu** (represented by the cog icon in the top-right corner of the AI Studio workspace).\n2.  Click **Export as ZIP** or **Export to GitHub**.\n3.  This package contains all configured files, including `package.json`, `vite.config.ts`, `tsconfig.json`, and the source code, ready for instant compilation (`npm install && npm run build`) or deployment."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 251434730
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
