  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining New Preset**\n\nI\'m working on a new preset, the `ELEGANT_DARK_CONFIG`. It\'s going to be elegant and dark, of course. Right now, I\'m figuring out what content to include to really capture that \"Elegant Dark\" aesthetic. I\'ve named it \"NorthByte Bistro\", ID `elegant_dark`.\n\n\n**Refining Color Palette**\n\nI\'ve nailed down the name as \"NorthByte Bistro.\" I\'m now honing the color palette: primary `#2563eb`, secondary `#4f46e5`, background `#030712`, textMuted `#94a3b8`, and accentGlow `rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.15)`. I\'m also looking into how to best insert the new config into `src/config/restaurant.config.ts`, considering its position relative to `defaultRestaurantConfig`.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Default Config**\n\nI\'ve decided to make `ELEGANT_DARK_CONFIG` the default by setting `defaultRestaurantConfig` equal to it. This will make the app launch with the \"Elegant Dark\" aesthetic right away. I\'m focusing now on ensuring the elegant design is fully implemented and beautiful. Specifically, I\'m working through the `RestaurantConfig` and finalizing the hero section, including title, subtitle, and call-to-action details and images.\n\n\n**Adding Signature Dishes**\n\nI\'ve been adding the signature dishes to `ELEGANT_DARK_CONFIG`, with images and descriptions. I\'ve included Wagyu A5 Striploin as a signature dish, alongside a couple of other options. I\'m focusing now on showcasing the dish details in an alluring way.\n\n\n**Finalizing Signature Dishes**\n\nI\'ve just added three signature dishes with details to `ELEGANT_DARK_CONFIG`: Wagyu A5 Striploin, Coastal Diver Scallops, and Deconstructed Lemon Sph\303\250re. I\'m focusing now on polishing the visual appeal of these featured dishes, ensuring they entice customers and fit with the elegant dark theme. I\'m also ensuring the associated data is included.\n\n\n**Expanding Menu Selection**\n\nI\'ve just added three more menu items to `ELEGANT_DARK_CONFIG`! These include \'Aged Foie Gras Terrine\', \'Artisanal Heirloom Burrata\', and \'Line-Caught Sea Bass\', each with images, descriptions, prices and tags. I\'m focusing on arranging these items in a way that feels refined and luxurious, to fit the elegant and dark theme.\n\n\n**Adding Drink Specials**\n\nI\'ve just added two new menu items to `ELEGANT_DARK_CONFIG`! These include \'Line-Caught Sea Bass\', \'Morel Mushroom Risotto\', and \'The Royal Sovereign\'. The dishes each have unique images, descriptions, prices and tags. I\'m focusing on arranging these items in a way that feels refined and luxurious, to fit the elegant and dark theme.\n\n\n\n**Curating Image Selections**\n\nI\'ve just been curating images for the `ELEGANT_DARK_CONFIG`, adding ambience, dishes, and behind-the-scenes photographs to the `images` array within the config. I\'m focusing on ensuring these visuals evoke the \"elegant dark\" theme, highlighting the luxury and precision of the restaurant. I am particularly considering the technical lighting precision of the images, as well as the obsidian finishes that are highlighted in the images.\n\n\n**Incorporating Chef\'s Background**\n\nI\'m now incorporating the chef\'s background and milestones into the `ELEGANT_DARK_CONFIG`! I\'ve added historical details about the chef and NorthByte, including training at Le Meurice, and leading a Michelin-star kitchen. I\'m focusing on the presentation and context, making sure this is a compelling narrative.\n\n\n**Adding Contact Information**\n\nI\'ve just added contact details and operating hours to `ELEGANT_DARK_CONFIG`! These include the phone, WhatsApp, email, address, and Google Maps embed URL. My focus now is on integrating this contact information seamlessly within the preset, ensuring it aligns with the overall \"elegant dark\" aesthetic and is easy to find. I\'m also ensuring the restaurant\'s opening hours are visible.\n\n\n**Adding Socials and SEO**\n\nI\'ve just been working on the `ELEGANT_DARK_CONFIG` SEO and social integration. I\'ve included Google Maps, socials like Instagram and Facebook, and SEO with meta title, description, keywords, and an OG image, and now, I\'m verifying the config\'s integration, considering icon imports. I\'m focusing on ensuring these elements are seamlessly incorporated within the preset and consistent.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now edit `src/config/restaurant.config.ts` to define the new `ELEGANT_DARK_CONFIG` based on the specified colors (obsidian dark `#030712`, vibrant cobalt blue `#2563eb`, and indigo `#4f46e5`) and make it the default preset. Let\'s apply this update."
